      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KOBY KEEPING (1) strongly fancied latest in a Grade 5 at this track and gave a big sight in front when second over 457m (25.65). Hits the ground running. Overdue and is among the main hopes. CODY'S STAR (2) boasts a strong record this journey with nine wins and four minors from 23 tries. Comes off a (29.90) win last time, scoring by 2.5 lengths in a OPEN over 510m at Rockhampton. Looks suited here and can measure up. EXEQUIEL (4) has a strong winning strike-rate this journey here having won two of three starts. In the money last time at Q Parklands (30.16) in a OPEN, finishing a 6 length third. Can hit the frame with the right run. MONTY ZOOMER (7) did a good job to finish third last time out over 457m at this track (25.73) in a Grade 5, the second top-three finish on the trot.",
